<li id="cite_note-56"><b><a href="#cite_ref-56" title="">^</a></b> Cf. <a href="#CITEREFKennefick2005" title="">Kennefick 2005</a> for the classic early measurements by the <a href="/wiki/Arthur_Eddington" title="Arthur Eddington" class="mw-redirect">Eddington</a> expeditions; for an overview of more recent measurements, see <a href="#CITEREFOhanianRuffini1994" title="">Ohanian &amp; Ruffini 1994</a>, chapter 4.3. For the most precise direct modern observations using quasars, cf. <a href="#CITEREFShapiroDavisLebachGregory2004" title="">Shapiro et al. 2004</a>.</li>
